message.content:
Below is a concise “map” of how the finished model is laid out and which dictionary blocks are used.  A good way to think of the build is as three main layers (arches at the bottom, cubes/half‐cylinders in the middle, and roofs/tall prisms at the top), with some tall pieces spanning more than one layer.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  TOTAL BLOCK COUNT AND LAYERS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
• Total Blocks: 13  
• Approx. 3 Layers (bottom arches, middle cubes/half‐cylinders, top roofs/tall prisms).

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  BLOCK‐BY‐BLOCK ARRANGEMENT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

BOTTOM (Layer 1):  
• Three Red Arches (#1), side by side left–to–right.

MIDDLE (Layer 2):  
• Left “Tower” Cube: One Blue Cube (#5) sitting on top of the left arch.  
• Right “Tower” Cube: One Orange Cube (#7) sitting on top of the right arch.  
• Center Cube: One Green Cube (#6), placed just behind (and between) the arches.  
• Two Yellow Half‐Cylinders (#14), side by side across the front “bridge” between left and right towers.

TOP (Layer 3) & TALL BACK PIECES:  
• Two Orange Wedges (#15) as roofs, one atop the Blue Cube, and one atop the Orange Cube.  
• Two Tall Yellow Prisms (#12), standing behind the Green Cube in the center.  
• One Tall Green Prism (#8), placed behind (to the rear of) the right tower.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  REQUIRED DICTIONARY BLOCKS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
• #1 (Red Arch) × 3  
• #5 (Blue Cube) × 1  
• #6 (Green Cube) × 1  
• #7 (Orange Cube) × 1  
• #8 (Tall Green Prism) × 1  
• #12 (Tall Yellow Prism) × 2  
• #14 (Yellow Half‐Cylinder) × 2  
• #15 (Orange “Roof” Wedge) × 2  

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
4)  SUGGESTED ASSEMBLY ORDER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
{  
   Step1:  Move block with index 1  (place first Red Arch, far left)  
   Step2:  Move block with index 1  (place second Red Arch, center)  
   Step3:  Move block with index 1  (place third Red Arch, far right)  
   Step4:  Move block with index 5  (place Blue Cube on left Arch)  
   Step5:  Move block with index 7  (place Orange Cube on right Arch)  
   Step6:  Move block with index 6  (place Green Cube behind center Arch)  
   Step7:  Move block with index 14 (place first Yellow Half‐Cylinder in front center)  
   Step8:  Move block with index 14 (place second Yellow Half‐Cylinder next to the first)  
   Step9:  Move block with index 12 (stand first Tall Yellow Prism behind Green Cube)  
   Step10: Move block with index 12 (stand second Tall Yellow Prism beside the first)  
   Step11: Move block with index 8  (stand Tall Green Prism behind right‐hand tower)  
   Step12: Move block with index 15 (place first Orange Roof Wedge on Blue Cube)  
   Step13: Move block with index 15 (place second Orange Roof Wedge on Orange Cube)  
}
